Template: rivendell-cloud-installer/install-type
Type: select
Choices: Standalone, Server, Client
Default: Standalone
Description: Rivendell installation type:
 Choose the Rivendell installation type. Standalone is recommended for most users.

Template: rivendell-cloud-installer/hostname
Type: string
Default: onair
Description: Hostname to set for the system:
 Rivendell requires the Linux hostname to match its configured hostname.
 Enter a value or leave as default "onair".

Template: rivendell-cloud-installer/set-timezone
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you want to set the timezone during install?
 If enabled, tzdata will be configured interactively.

Template: rivendell-cloud-installer/enable-ufw
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Enable UFW firewall and open required ports?
 You can later adjust rules with ufw.

Template: rivendell-cloud-installer/harden-ssh
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Harden SSH by disabling password authentication?
 Ensure your SSH key login works before enabling this.

Template: rivendell-cloud-installer/create-rd-user
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Create the 'rd' user if running as root?
 If false, the current sudo user will be used as the primary operator.

Template: rivendell-cloud-installer/install-mate
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Install MATE desktop environment?
 Use only if your system lacks a desktop and you want MATE.
